title: A Popular History of Ireland: from the Earliest Period to the Emancipation of the Catholics, Book 09
creator: Thomas D'Arcy McGee
description: LibriVox recording of The Popular History of Ireland Book 09, by Thomas D'Arcy McGee, read by Sibella Denton. Thomas D'Arcy McGee was an Irish refugee and a father of the Canadian confederation. His work on Irish history is comprehensive, encompassing twelve books; Book 9 subtitled “From the Accession of James I Till the Death of Cromwell”, addresses the early Stuart period’s unsettled history and the actions of that person, who, seen from the Irish perspective, was certainly one of the most villainous of men: Cromwell. (Summary by Sibella Denton) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org M4B audiobook of Complete Series
